# Python Standards

- Python 3.14+ — use modern syntax (type hints, `match`, `|` union types)
- Use `pathlib.Path` for all file paths, never `os.path`
- SQL queries use parameterized placeholders (`?`), never f-strings
- Every analytics/ML function returns a `pd.DataFrame`
- Database connections via `src/data_generation/schema.get_connection()` — never construct connections manually
- Imports: stdlib → third-party → project modules, separated by blank lines
- No wildcard imports
- Docstrings on public functions (one-liner or numpy-style for complex ones)
